<article>
    <h1>Kia de&#xAD;vel&#xAD;op&#xAD;ing open-top, all-ter&#xAD;rain ve&#xAD;hi&#xAD;cle</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201031/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-10-31"><time>2020-10-31</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE MOTORING</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Kia is de­vel­op­ing a stan­dard plat­form for its next gen­er­a­tion of 2.5- and 5-tonne mil­i­tary ve­hi­cles, with pro­to­typ­ing to be­gin within this year.</p>
    <p>An open-top, all-ter­rain ve­hi­cle (right) un­der devel­op­ment is based on the chas­sis of the Mo­have, a large Kia SUV sold in the United States.</p>
    <p>Kia aims to of­fer its new range from 2024. The large-scale pro­gramme will see the re­place­ment of 2.5-tonne and 5-tonne mil­i­tary ve­hi­cles cur­rently in oper­a­tion, and the devel­op­ment of new 5-tonne bul­let­proof ve­hi­cles.</p>
    <p>The stan­dard ve­hi­cles will be equipped with a range of the lat­est com­mer­cial tech­nolo­gies, in­clud­ing high-torque, 7-litre diesel en­gines with au­to­matic trans­mis­sion, anti-lock­ing brak­ing sys­tem, anti-spin reg­u­la­tor, park­ing as­sist, 360-de­gree cam­era and nav­i­ga­tion.</p>

